cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.CG

Reasoning: The paper deals with parameterised space complexity classes and their counting variants, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. The use of parameterised logarithmic space and the introduction of new classes based on tail-nondeterminism make cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely sub-category. The study of natural problems on graphs and digraphs suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories. The analysis of closure properties and arithmetic operations is related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), while the study of branching programs and the complexity of the determinant function suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category.
